## Git Branching and merging 

// List out all the local branches 
Git branch

// Creating a new branch 
git branch <branch_name>

// switch to an existing branch 
git checkout  <branch_name>

// Create and switch to new branch in one command
git checkout -b <branch_name>

// Delete a local branch 
git branch -d <branch_name>

// Forced delete the local branch with unmerged changes
git branch -D <branch_name>

// merge the specificied branch history into current branch
git merge <branch_name>

// cancel a merge that resulted in a conflict
git merge --abort


## Remote Repositories 

// list all remote repositories 
git remote -v

// add new remote repository with a url 
git add remote <name> <repo_url>     -  name can be like origin by default 

// download latest changes from the repository without merging them 
git fetch <remote>

// fetch and merge remote changes into current branch
git pull

// uploads local branch commit to remote repository 
git push <remote> <branch_name>

// push a new local branch to the remote repository 
git push -u <remote> <branch_name>

//delete branch on the remote repository 
git push <remote> --delete <branch_name>